f5466ba8d59161915605f6%2Fhighest2lowest-feature-11061f-f.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8640x4860+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F63%2F1d%2F8a7736f5466ba8d59161915605f6%2Fhighest2lowest-feature-11061f-f.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8640x4860+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F63%2F1d%2F8a7736f5466ba8d59161915605f6%2Fhighest2lowest-feature-11061f-f.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8640x4860+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F63%2F1d%2F8a7736f5466ba8d59161915605f6%2Fhighest2lowest-feature-11061f-f.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8640x4860+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F63%2F1d%2F8a7736f5466ba8d59161915605f6%2Fhighest2lowest-feature-11061f-f.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8640x4860+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F63%2F1d%2F8a7736f5466ba8d59161915605f6%2Fhighest2lowest-feature-11061f-f.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8640x4860+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F63%2F1d%2F8a7736f5466ba8d59161915605f6%2Fhighest2lowest-feature-11061f-f.jpg" class="img" alt="Denzel Washington stars as music executive David King in Spike Lee&amp;#039;s Highest 2 Lowest." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Denzel Washington stars as music executive David King in Spike Lee's &lt;em&gt;Highest 2 Lowest. &lt;/em&gt;                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          David Lee                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies:&lt;/strong&gt; Denzel Washington returns to the big screen as music mogul David King in the crime thriller &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/14/nx-s1-5501377/highest-2-lowest-teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-weapons" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Highest 2 Lowest&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. In the movie, his family gets caught up in a complicated ransom plot.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/12/nx-s1-5496323/alien-earth-review-fx" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Alien: Earth&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; serves as a prequel to the &lt;em&gt;Alien&lt;/em&gt; movies, exploring recurring themes, such as whether technological advancements are designed to benefit humans or ultimately replace them, says NPR TV critic Eric Deggans.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books: &lt;/strong&gt;Aisha Muharrar's debut novel, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/12/nx-s1-5489718/new-books-this-week-karin-slaughter" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Loved One&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, follows Julia, who is grieving the loss of her best friend Gabe. She takes on the awkward quest of finding and returning his missing things for his mom.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music: &lt;/strong&gt;Audrey Hobert, who began her career writing for a Nickelodeon sitcom, is switching gears for her debut album, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/13/nx-s1-5492315/audrey-hobert-whos-the-clown-interview" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Who's the Clown?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; NPR's Isabella Gomez Sarmiento says it is a bubblegum pop record with goofy yet vulnerable lyrics.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-82683" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6000;         --source-height: 3375;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F47%2F626a4bfc4da485416eed115f69db%2Fgettyimages-2226566236.jpg" class="img" alt="Venus Williams celebrates after winning a women&amp;#039;s single match against Peyton Stearns during on day 2 of the Mubadala Citi DC Open on July 22 in Washington, DC." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Venus Williams celebrates after winning a women's single match against Peyton Stearns during on day 2 of the Mubadala Citi DC Open on July 22 in Washington, DC.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Scott Taetsch/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;At 45, tennis legend Venus Williams is &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/14/g-s1-82681/venus-williams-u-s-open-oldest-player" target="_blank"&gt;making history in her return&lt;/a&gt; to the U.S. Open this month as the oldest singles player in over four decades.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Southern food chain Bojangles announced plans to open a total of 55 locations across the Big Apple and New Jersey over the next decade. The first restaurant will &lt;a href="https://gothamist.com/news/bojangles-is-coming-back-to-nyc-starting-in-brooklyn" target="_blank"&gt;open later this year&lt;/a&gt;. (via &lt;a href="https://gothamist.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Gothamist&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The origins of the Word of the Week — "dog" — remain a mystery, but over a millennia ago it was used as an insult. Here is how the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/13/nx-s1-5500476/dog-history-etymology-origin" target="_blank"&gt;meaning of the word has changed&lt;/a&gt; over time.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
