.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+873/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fac%2F3c%2F85377f3b4b5097c32bc845e51e17%2F186071607-20250208-111044.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+873/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fac%2F3c%2F85377f3b4b5097c32bc845e51e17%2F186071607-20250208-111044.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+873/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fac%2F3c%2F85377f3b4b5097c32bc845e51e17%2F186071607-20250208-111044.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+873/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fac%2F3c%2F85377f3b4b5097c32bc845e51e17%2F186071607-20250208-111044.jpg" class="img" alt="A squirrel is seen looking straight into the camera lens while sitting in the hole of a tree." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A squirrel peering out of a hole in a tree.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Keri Olson                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Every day, 67-year-old Keri Olson of Baraboo, Wis., takes two-hour walks, pulling out her phone and snapping pictures of the scenery that gives her joy. The activity helps quiet her mind, allowing her to be present in the moment, which is how she caught this glimpse of a squirrel watching her from a hole in a tree. They both stood completely still for several minutes, studying each other. "It was a sacred, fleeting moment of connection," Olson said.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Olson's tip: &lt;/strong&gt;"Be fully present, be open to experiencing something that will fill you with wonder, and be ready to capture something that fascinates you and brings you joy."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-82935" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 960;         --source-height: 540;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/1200/qualit