om%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/960x540+0+182/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff4%2Fbc%2Fb19e4a474aa6a291bfcebf14ad7c%2F186071607-prince-william-sound-sea-kayak-1.jpg" class="img" alt="The tip of a red kayak sits in the water. A gray kayak sits in the water to the right. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Shawn Peterson sits in a kayak during a journey with his friend Stephen Barnes.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Shawn Peterson                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Shawn Peterson captured his favorite shot during a three-hour crossing on a 10-day sea kayaking route through the glacial fjords of Prince William Sound in the Gulf of Alaska. Ten inches of rain fell during the 42-year-old's August 2016 trip. During his journey, Peterson was simultaneously soaked and mesmerized by the raindrops undulating across the water. This photo is special to him because it represents a life-changing experience with his friend Stephen Barnes.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Peterson's tip:&lt;/strong&gt; "Enjoy the moment!"&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;About the people&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-82582" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6000;         --source-height: 3375;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+5/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F19%2F0d%2Fdafa5ab84dbf927cc0249c7f821d%2F186071607-mike-sizemore-20150805-084-pyongyang-kp-kim-il-sung-square.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+5/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1