/crop/6000x3375+0+5/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F19%2F0d%2Fdafa5ab84dbf927cc0249c7f821d%2F186071607-mike-sizemore-20150805-084-pyongyang-kp-kim-il-sung-square.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+5/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F19%2F0d%2Fdafa5ab84dbf927cc0249c7f821d%2F186071607-mike-sizemore-20150805-084-pyongyang-kp-kim-il-sung-square.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+5/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F19%2F0d%2Fdafa5ab84dbf927cc0249c7f821d%2F186071607-mike-sizemore-20150805-084-pyongyang-kp-kim-il-sung-square.jpg" class="img" alt="Two kids play in Kim II Sung Square " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Two kids play in Kim II Sung Square.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Mike Sizemore                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It is no surprise to Mike Sizemore that it is hot in Pyongyang, North Korea, in August. One afternoon, the 44-year-old from Charleston, W.Va., and his guides stood at the end of Kim II Sung Square, hoping for a breeze as they watched hundreds of schoolchildren practice for an Independence Day celebration later that month. The kids took a quick break. Everything was quiet for a moment, then two girls leaped to their feet and started chasing one another around, laughing and shouting. Many years later, Sizemore still sometimes thinks about them and hopes their spirits remain unbroken. "Wherever you go, it's people. It's always about the people," Sizemore said. "Among the photos I've taken, my favorites are of individuals just getting through the day."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sizemore's tip:&lt;/strong&gt; "Look around. Take all the photos you can. Every photo captures a piece of today, and tomorrow, even a mediocre photo might make someone pause and say, 'Wow!'"&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Love for home&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-82620" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4284;         --source-height: 2410;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/d