://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4284x2410+0+1354/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F69%2Fb3ba61d84b85aadd1c08f9f6963d%2F186071607-img-2921.jpeg" class="img" alt="A bacon, egg and cheese like no other." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A bacon, egg and cheese like no other.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Sabrina Hyman                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This photo may appear to be just an ordinary bacon, egg and cheese on a roll, but it is not. To 31-year-old Sabrina Hyman of Virginia, it is home. She says this homemade Long Island Kaiser roll with Boar's Head bacon and cheese and homegrown eggs cannot be replicated anywhere else other than certain places on Long Island. She no longer lives there because of the high cost of living. "This picture resembles the housing market on Long Island for me: out of reach, but once I get my hands on one when I go back to visit, it's like striking gold," Hyman said.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hyman's tip: "&lt;/strong&gt;Stop saying, 'I'll take a picture on the way back.' If you have that moment now, take it."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Familial bonds&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-82947" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1780;         --source-height: 1001;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1780x1001+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F36%2F34737d734ec5b0eaf5c7a37f3df4%2F186071607-r-shawn-bohs-npr.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1780x1001+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F36%2F34737d734ec5b0eaf5c7a37f3df4%2F186071607-r-shawn-bohs-npr.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1780x1001+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2