016d11e.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg" class="img" alt="Why are people over 50 eager to re-enter the dating pool?" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Overall divorce rates are down except for one key demographic: people over 50. This phenomenon is called gray divorce. As we get older, it's common to hear about how much harder it is to make friends or build new relationships. But Gen Xers spent most of their adulthood living in a society where divorce is viewed as more acceptable and less stigmatized. That's one reason why they're open to starting new chapters. In this episode of &lt;em&gt;It's Been A Minute&lt;/em&gt;, host Brittany Luse &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5494232:nx-s1-9399221" target="_blank"&gt;discusses gray divorce&lt;/a&gt; and how it's never too late to write a new love story.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Weekend picks&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-79458" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4425;         --source-height: 2489;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg" class="img" alt="Big Freedia on the steps outside of Esplanade Studios in New Orleans, which was converted from a church, on July 15, 2025." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Big Freedia poses for a portrait on July 15 at Esplanade Studios in New Orleans, LA. The studio was converted from a church.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Claire Harbage/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies:&lt;/strong&gt; In the horror film &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5299179:nx-s1-9395906" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Together&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Alison Brie and Dave Franco play a couple whose bodies start fusing together after they visit a mysterious cave. The film explores toxic codependency.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;Wednesday&lt;/em&gt; is back for a second season this week. To help prepare for the new episodes, &lt;em&gt;Pop Culture Happy Hour&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5492150:nx-s1-9396551" target="_blank"&gt;revisits their conversation about Wednesday Addams&lt;/a&gt;, who moves from her home to the gloomy Nevermore Academy.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/05/nx-s1-5491598/new-books-this-week" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Manga: A New History of Japanese Comics&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; examines Japan's eye-catching graphic storytelling style. The book chronicles the evolution of manga from its late 19th-century origins to its popularity today.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music: &lt;/strong&gt;Big Freedia's new album, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/05/nx-s1-5340730/big-freedia-takes-bounce-music-to-church-on-new-album-pressing-onward" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pressing Onward&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, fuses gospel and her love for bounce music, which she helped popularize. NPR's Ari Shapiro speaks with her about how singing in church as a child &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/05/nx-s1-5340730/big-freedia-takes-bounce-music-to-church-on-new-album-pressing-onward" target="_blank"&gt;led her to this moment&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍲 Food:&lt;/strong&gt; Social media influencers are bringing back recession-era recipes to help people cook cheap, easy and filling meals. Check out some videos and &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5477546/recipes-tiktok" target="_blank"&gt;try one for yourself&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓ Quiz:&lt;/strong&gt; I was so close to 100%! I missed one question, yet again. Can you beat my high score? &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/08/g-s1-81265/trump-fitness-test-democrats-texas-zoo-quiz-news" target="_blank"&gt;Test your knowledge&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-81503" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6016;         --source-height: 3384;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg" class="img" alt="&amp;#039;Superman&amp;#039; spinoff TV actor Dean Cain at a convention in Chicago. The actor shared an Instagram post on Wednesday about his plan to join ICE and urged his followers to join too." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 'Superman' spinoff TV actor Dean Cain at a convention in Chicago. The actor shared an Instagram post on Wednesday about his plan to join ICE and urged his followers to join too.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Rob Grabowski/Invision/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Actor Dean Cain will be &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5495436/superman-tv-actor-dean-cain-joins-ice-recruit-immigration" target="_blank"&gt;sworn in as an honorary officer&lt;/a&gt; with U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement, according to the Department of Homeland Security. He is best known for his starring role in &lt;em&gt;Lois &amp; Clark: The New Adventures of Superman&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Martha's Vineyard African American Film Festival is now in its 23rd year, offering a platform for Black artists to showcase their ambitious projects. NPR's Eric Deggans notes that the event &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5494472/marthas-vineyard-african-american-film-festival-obama-slick-rick" target="_blank"&gt;highlights works centered on Black life&lt;/a&gt; that few other festivals might recognize or encourage.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New York City officials announced that the remains of three more victims of the 9/11 terror attacks were &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5495481/three-more-9-11-nyc-victims-identified" target="_blank"&gt;identified using advanced DNA-analysis techniques&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
